<div class="os-raise-graybox">
<h5>Horizontal Dilations of a Function</h5>
<p>A horizontal stretch or compression “transforms” the parent function into another function by horizontally dilating the graph by “b” units. </p>
<p align="center"> Horizontal Dilation → \( f(bx) \)</p>
</div>
<br/>
<p>If the \(b\) value is negative, the graph is reflected over the \(y\)-axis. If the \(b\) value is greater than 1, the graph is horizontally compressed. If the \(b\) value is between 0 and 1, the graph is horizontally stretched.</p>